wiki.summary: “Field Trip” is the third track from VULTURES 2 featuring Playboi Carti, Don Toliver and Kodak Black. The first snippet of the song surfaced on February 11, 2024. An extended snippet of Don’s vocals surfaced the following day on February 12, 2024. Two more snippets (one of a rough Ye verse and the other for Carti’s verse) surfaced on March 5, 2024. The song was played at a friends and family listening party in Los Angeles on March 9, 2024, and once again on March 11, 2024, at a listening party in Arizona. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: “Field Trip” is the third track from VULTURES 2 featuring Playboi Carti, Don Toliver and Kodak Black. The first snippet of the song surfaced on February 11, 2024. An extended snippet of Don’s vocals surfaced the following day on February 12, 2024. Two more snippets (one of a rough Ye verse and the other for Carti’s verse) surfaced on March 5, 2024. The song was played at a friends and family listening party in Los Angeles on March 9, 2024, and once again on March 11, 2024, at a listening party in Arizona. Wheezy, the producer of “FIELD TRIP” played a short portion of the song on Instagram Live on March 15, 2024. He previously had teased the track on Instagram with the caption “Took her on a Field trip 🌊🧛🏽‍♂️🌊🧛🏽‍♂️🔥🔥🔥”. On March 17, 2024, Don Toliver brought out Ty Dolla $ign at Rolling Loud LA and they performed a portion of “FIELD TRIP” together. Read more on Last.fm.
